# Theme: Kleene-star fixed points, including a history-producing action.
# Source: Kleene algebra axioms and derivative treatment of star in the paper.
# Property left-unfold: Zero iterations or one action followed by more iterations.
# Property right-unfold: The symmetric right-unfold law.
# Property star-idempotent: Iterating an already iterated action adds no histories.
# Property add-id-under-star: Explicit skip is already supplied by star.
# Property drop-star-is-id: Repeating an impossible action only permits zero iterations.
# Property one-dup-is-not-all: A finite approximation misses histories with two or more dups.
# Property positive-dups-two-forms: Both sides generate every positive number of dups.
# Property even-dups-not-all: Repeating pairs generates only even history growth.
check left-unfold: dup* == id + dup . dup*;
check right-unfold: dup* == id + dup* . dup;
check star-idempotent: dup* . dup* == dup*;
check add-id-under-star: (id + dup)* == dup*;
check drop-star-is-id: drop* == id;
check one-dup-is-not-all: dup* == id + dup;
check positive-dups-two-forms: dup . dup* == dup* . dup;
check even-dups-not-all: (dup . dup)* == dup*;
